# semgrep path exclusions.
#
# NOTE: creating this file REPLACES semgrep's built-in default .semgrepignore
# (it is not merged), so the default entries are replicated first.
#
# --- semgrep defaults (keep in sync with upstream defaults) ---------------
node_modules/
build/
dist/
vendor/
.env/
.venv/
.tox/
*.min.js
test/
tests/
.semgrep
.semgrep_logs
# Generated / vendored artifacts of this repo
coverage/
cdk.out/
.stryker-tmp/

# --- Reviewed false positives --------------------------------------------
# 1) Unit test asserting the local in-process HTTP test server; connects to
#    http://127.0.0.1 by design (TLS not applicable). Consistent with semgrep's
#    default philosophy of excluding test dirs (this repo uses Jest-style
#    __tests__/, which the default list does not cover).
docker/__tests__/server-runtime.test.js
# 2) Skill helper scripts flagged by use-defused-xml. Both guard the stdlib
#    parser with ensure_safe_xml_source() (rejects DOCTYPE/ENTITY declarations,
#    caps input size — blocks XXE and XML bombs; verified with attack payloads).
#    defusedxml cannot be imported: the container runs skill scripts with the
#    base-image python3 and has no pip / third-party Python deps by design.
docker/skills/lark-doc/scripts/doc_word_stat.py
docker/skills/lark-slides/scripts/xml_text_overlap_lint.py
